FBIS4-43444 "drweu117_n_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 NORDIC COUNTRIES Sweden Environment Minister Johansson Resigns Environment Minister Johansson Resigns Oresund Bridge Plan Cited LD1606131394 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Swedish 1300 GMT 16 Jun 94 LD1606131394 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network Swedish BFN [Text] Olof Johansson, Swedish environment minister and chairman of the Center Party, has resigned from the government. Environment Minister Johansson resigned after Prime Minister Carl Bildt decided that the Government of Sweden will approve the construction of the Oresund bridge. It is not known yet whether the other Center Party ministers in the government will resign.
